// Spectral Chord Resonator acceptance notes.
//
// The Cmajor 1.0.3066 CLI pinned in this repo uses .cmajtest files for its
// built-in test runner; it does not ship the std.test-style .test harness named
// in the implementation brief. The executable acceptance tests for this patch
// are therefore in tests/test_spectral_chord_resonator_probe.py, where the
// generated Cmajor JavaScript runtime is rendered and measured. A native
// cmaj-runner audio input passthrough fixture also lives at
// tests/spectral_chord_resonator/SpectralChordResonator.cmajtest.
//
// Listening checks:
// - Resonance: send a click into audioIn, hold MIDI note 57, set feedback
//   high and phase feedback to 1.0. The rendered tail should ring at 220 Hz.
// - Chord change: move held MIDI notes while the source audio is active. The old
//   bins should decay through damping; spectrumState is not cleared.
// - Parameter sweep: sweep magFeedbackIn while noise and a held chord are active.
//   The 50 ms SmoothedValue ramp should avoid zipper noise.
